Most 1 H and 13 C NMR signals for 7–8 were doubled due to the presence of a formamide group ( Tables 2 and 4 ). The 1D NMR signals were separated into the s- cis and s- trans forms based on the formamide chemical shifts as well as HSQC spectra (
,
;
