The cytotoxicities of compounds 1–8 against the human leukemia K562, normal human hepatocytes L-02, human pancreatic cancer ASPC- 1, human lung carcinoma H69AR, and human breast cancer MDA-MB-231 cell lines were evaluated (
;
). The bioactive results showed that three compounds exhibited cytotoxicity (IC 50 < 10 μM) against the selected cell lines ( Table 5 ). Compounds 3 and 5 exhibited cytotoxicity against K562 cell line with IC 50 values of 6.4 and 6.3 μM, respectively. The IC 50 values of compounds 5 and 8 against MDA-MB-231 cell line were 7.3 and 7.9 μM, respectively.
